HEADWORD: Hatchway
<hw>Hatch"way`</hw> <pr>(-w⟦amac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A square or
oblong opening in a deck or floor, affording passage from one deck or
story to another; the entrance to a cellar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

